#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:4
msgid "command - run a program"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:9
msgid "command [OPTIONS] [COMMANDNAME [ARG ...]]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:16
msgid ""
"**command** forces the shell to execute the program *COMMANDNAME* and ignore "
"any functions or builtins with the same name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:18
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:20
msgid "**-a** or **--all**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:21
msgid "Prints all *COMMAND* found in :envvar:`PATH`, in the order found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:23
msgid "**-q** or **--query**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:24
msgid ""
"Silence output and print nothing, setting only exit status. Implies **--"
"search**. For compatibility, this is also **--quiet** (deprecated)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:28
msgid "**-v** (or **-s** or **--search**)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:29
msgid ""
"Prints the external command that would be executed, or prints nothing if no "
"file with the specified name could be found in :envvar:`PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:31
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:32
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:34
msgid ""
"With the **-v** option, ``command`` treats every argument as a separate "
"command to look up and sets the exit status to 0 if any of the specified "
"commands were found, or 127 if no commands could be found. **--quiet** used "
"with **-v** prevents commands being printed, like ``type -q``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:37
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:39
msgid ""
"``command ls`` executes the ``ls`` program, even if an ``ls`` function also "
"exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:40
msgid "``command -s ls`` prints the path to the ``ls`` program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/command.rst:41
msgid ""
"``command -q git; and command git log`` runs ``git log`` only if ``git`` "
"exists."
msgstr ""
